title: Starship program prepares for major test with 33 engine Static Fire
summary: SpaceX’s Starship program is set to attempt a major milestone ahead of its historic launch with a full-set 33-engine test of Booster 7.

title: Russian Progress resupply ship launches on flight to space station
summary: A Russian Soyuz rocket blasted off Thursday from the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan, boosting a Progress resupply ship into orbit in pursuit of the International Space Station with more than 5,500 pounds of cargo, fuel, water, and air.

title: Progress MS-22 resupply ship launches to ISS
summary: Roscosmos has launched its next Progress resupply craft to the International Space Station (ISS). Liftoff of the Progress MS-22 mission occurred at 06:15 UTC on Feb. 9 from Site 31/6 at the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan aboard a Soyuz-2.1a rocket. It will spend two days performing maneuvers until it docks with the ISS on Feb. 11.

title: Watch live: Russian Progress resupply ship ready for launch to space station
summary: A Russian Soyuz rocket is ready for blastoff Wednesday from the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan, boosting a Progress resupply ship into orbit in pursuit of the International Space Station with more than 5,500 pounds of cargo, fuel, water, and air. Liftoff is set for 1:15 a.m. EST (0615 GMT).

title: NASA Awards Environmental Compliance, Operations Contract
summary: NASA has selected Navarro Research and Engineering, Inc., of Oak Ridge, Tennessee, for the Environmental Compliance and Operations 3 (ECO3) contract, which provides environmental restoration program services and other support at the agency’s White Sands Test Facility in Las Cruces, New Mexico.

title: SpaceX prepares for a massive test this week: Firing all 33 Starship engines at once
summary: WASHINGTON – SpaceX President Gwynne Shotwell said Wednesday the company plans to attempt a major Starship milestone this week.

title: NASA Selects Scientific Support for Goddard Institute of Space Studies
summary: NASA has selected Autonomic Integra of Gaithersburg, Maryland, for specialized scientific support services to the Goddard Institute for Space Studies (GISS) in New York.

title: NASA's Curiosity Finds Surprise Clues to Mars' Watery Past
summary: Among other discoveries made by the rover, rippled rock textures suggest lakes existed in a region of ancient Mars that scientists expected to be drier.
